One can admire her as a person for her courage, intellect, determination and ambition, but she divided the nation politically
Sir, Whether you agreed or disagreed with her political decisions there is no doubt about Margaret Thatcher’s strength of character, her love of Britain and her dignity of person.
There are some who would do well to take a leaf from Mrs Thatcher’s book and learn to value strength of character, dignity and respect: qualities which add immeasurably to harmony and strength in society but which, regrettably, are lacking in Britain and elsewhere today.
